"We have to get active now," he said on the issue of startup.
"It's a historic moment."
The app uses Solid's technology to enable users to create their own personal online data storage or POD.
It can contain contact lists, task lists, a calendar, a music library and other tools for the private and corporate sector.
Similar to Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify all content is available in one browser and at the same time.
The special thing about the personal online data storage is that the user can decide alone who can access which data.
The company describes this concept as personal reinforcement and development via data.
According to CEO John Bruce, the idea behind this is that the company uses resources, processes and corresponding capabilities to ensure that solid is available to all.
The company currently includes Berners-Lee, Bruce, some developers who have been hired to work on this project, as well as a community of voluntary programmers. Furthermore, a security platform acquired by IBM is used.
With the beginning of this week, technology developers worldwide can create their own decentralized apps with the tools available on the Inrupt website.
